excerpt: Urban public site on 26 acres with sports areas, an amphitheater, a swimming pool, a library & more.
detail_description: Miri City Fan Recreation Park is a sprawling 26-acre urban public space that offers a variety of recreational activities. Visitors can enjoy sports facilities, an amphitheater, swimming pool, and even a library within the park. It's a popular destination for both locals and tourists looking to unwind and engage in leisurely pursuits. Whether you're interested in sports or simply want to relax amidst greenery, Miri City Fan has something for everyone.
name: Miri City Fan Recreation Park

excerpt: 22-acre facility featuring crocodile breeding areas & a mini zoo with exotic birds & mammals.
detail_description: Miri Crocodile Farm Wildlife Mini Zoo is a 22-acre facility in Miri, Malaysia. It is the first and largest crocodile farm in the northern region of Sarawak. The farm features natural breeding enclosures and sanctuary ponds for over 1,000 Estuarine Crocodiles and Malayan Gharials.
name: Miri Crocodile Farm Wildlife Mini Zoo
address: Lot 164, Jalan Lutong - Kuala Baram, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Tusan Beach Subis, located about 40 km from Miri City, is renowned for its mesmerizing Blue Tears phenomenon. While it may be challenging to reach without a car, the beach offers a serene and romantic atmosphere, perfect for solo or couple visits. Visitors can savor a refreshing coconut shake while enjoying the calming sea breeze. However, it's important to watch out for steep stairs and be mindful of keeping the beach clean.
name: TUSAN BEACH SUBIS
address: Unnamed Road,, Kampung Terahat, 98150 Bekenu, Sarawak, Malaysia

excerpt: Well-known national park & prehistoric site featuring dramatic limestone caves & rock paintings.
detail_description: Niah National Park is a renowned national park and prehistoric site that boasts impressive limestone caves and ancient rock paintings. It holds the distinction of being home to the oldest modern human remains in Southeast Asia, dating back 40,000 years, making it one of the most significant archaeological sites globally. Visitors can witness a captivating natural spectacle as swiftlets return to their nests at sunset while bats fly out foraging in the forest.
name: Niah National Park

excerpt: Historic derrick serving as monument to discovery of oil in 1910, located on museum grounds.
detail_description: Perched atop Canada Hill in Miri, Malaysia, the Miri Oil Well No.1 (Grand Old Lady) stands as a significant historical landmark. This iconic derrick marks the site of the first oil well in Malaysia, symbolizing nearly a century of petroleum history. Although it is no longer operational, this well holds great cultural and historical value and has been designated as a protected historical site by the Sarawak Government.
name: Miri Oil Well No.1 (Grand Old Lady)
address: The Grand Old Lady - Canada Hill, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Miri Handicraft Centre is the perfect spot to discover genuine souvenirs beyond the typical touristy items. It showcases a wide array of crafts created by Malaysia's indigenous communities, including handwoven bags, traditional headwear, and authentic Malaysian attire. If you're seeking unique mementos that reflect local artistry, this center is a must-visit.
name: Miri Handicraft Centre

excerpt: Museum focusing on local petroleum history, with replicas, interactive exhibits & a historic tower.
detail_description: The Petroleum Museum in Miri, Sarawak is a significant attraction that delves into the local petroleum history. It features replicas, interactive exhibits, and a historic tower. The museum's outdoor display showcases an oil derrick and nodding donkey, highlighting Sarawak's oil industry timeline. Inside, visitors can explore an earthquake simulator, model oil rig, and traditional oil extraction methods.
name: Petroleum Museum, Miri, Sarawak.
address: Jabatan Muzium Sarawak, Canada Hill, Jln Oil Well No. 1, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Canada Hill is a prominent landmark in Miri, Sarawak, offering breathtaking panoramic views of the city and its surroundings. Visitors can explore the iconic Grand Old Lady, an oil rig that played a significant role in the region's petroleum industry. The hill provides a perfect spot for leisurely strolls or picnics while enjoying the cool breeze and stunning sunsets. Additionally, it is a popular spot for paragliding enthusiasts, adding an adventurous element to the experience.
name: Canada Hill

detail_description: Coco Cabana, located in Marina Bay, Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia, is a popular waterfront destination known for its relaxed atmosphere and stunning surroundings. It offers a blend of art, entertainment, and coastal beauty. Visitors can enjoy the beach, sample local cuisine at food stalls, and experience live music and art events. The site is renowned for its breathtaking sunset views and features a striking seahorse lighthouse.
name: Coco Cabana
address: Lot 2260, Jln Bandaraya, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Tua Pek Kong Temple, situated on River Road near the Fish Market, is a significant cultural and religious landmark in Miri. Constructed in 1913 by Chinese traders as an expression of gratitude to their deities, it stands as the city's oldest surviving building from World War II. The temple's intricate and vibrant architecture makes it a captivating place of worship for visitors. Its historical value is evident as it holds deep cultural significance for the local community.
name: Tua Pek Kong Temple

excerpt: Miri is a Malaysian city on the northwest coast of the island of Borneo. At the Petroleum Museum, on Canada Hill, hands-on exhibits explore the regionâ€™s oil history. Outside is the Grand Old Lady, a 1910 oil well and local landmark. In the city center, vendors at Pasar Raya and Tamu Muhibbah markets offer fresh produce and handicrafts. Tua Pek Kong Temple has pillars carved with golden dragons.
detail_description: Miri is a city located in Malaysia on the island of Borneo. The Petroleum Museum on Canada Hill showcases the region's oil history, featuring interactive exhibits and the iconic Grand Old Lady, a historic oil well. Visitors can explore Pasar Raya and Tamu Muhibbah markets in the city center for fresh produce and local crafts. The Tua Pek Kong Temple boasts intricately carved pillars adorned with golden dragons.
name: Miri

excerpt: Jungle area known for its limestone cave & archaeological site with cave paintings.
detail_description: Gua Niah, located in Sarawak, Malaysia, is a jungle area renowned for its limestone caves and archaeological sites featuring cave paintings. The site offers a nice hiking experience with three caves to explore along a long but not too difficult trail. It's advisable to carry sufficient water and flashlights when exploring the caves. The trek is well-maintained and there are refreshments available at the nearby canteen.
name: Gua Niah (Niah Caves) Entrance, Niah, Sarawak.

detail_description: Tamu Muhibbah is a bustling market located near the central station, offering a wide array of local products from the Sarawakian interior. Visitors can immerse themselves in the vibrant atmosphere while browsing through an assortment of items such as sweet pineapples, tapioca tubers, dried fish, spices, handicrafts, and produce from upriver areas.
name: Tamu Muhibbah

detail_description: Sky Garden Dining Miri is a delightful culinary destination that offers an exceptional dining experience amidst stunning views. Nestled in the heart of Miri, this restaurant combines a vibrant atmosphere with a diverse menu that caters to various tastes. Guests can enjoy both local and international dishes while soaking in the breathtaking scenery from its elevated location. The ambiance is perfect for casual gatherings or special occasions, making it a must-visit spot for food enthusiasts looking to indulge in delicious meals surrounded by nature's beauty.
name: Sky Garden Dining Miri
address: Meritz Hotel 17th Floor, Lot 1079, Block 9, MCLD, Jalan Miri Pujut, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Luak Esplanade, situated just 15 minutes from Miri Tourism City, is a serene recreational area offering various attractions and a peaceful environment for leisurely activities. The esplanade provides opportunities for social and family gatherings such as BBQs, picnics, and camping by the beautiful beach. Visitors can also enjoy leisurely walks along the seaside promenade while taking in the scenic views and cool sea breeze.
name: Luak Esplanade

excerpt: Ridge summit reachable via a hiking circuit, offering views over the city, sea & a lush valley.
detail_description: Perched atop Canada Hill, The Grand Old Lady is a historic site in Miri, marking Malaysia's first oil well. It stands as a testament to the region's petroleum history and has been designated as a protected historical landmark by the Sarawak Government. Visitors often combine their trip with a hike to the summit ridge, which offers breathtaking panoramic views of the city, sea, and verdant valleys.
name: The Grand Old Lady - Canada Hill

detail_description: Located at the Saberkas Commercial Centre, the Saberkas Night Market is a vibrant and bustling market that operates from Thursday to Sunday evenings. With over 170 stalls, visitors can find a variety of items such as household goods, fresh produce, local handicrafts, and more.
name: Saberkas Night Market
address: Pasar malam seberkas, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

excerpt: National park with the largest lake in Sarawak, for fishing & boat trips in forested environs.
detail_description: Loagan Bunut National Park, nestled in Miri, Sarawak, is a treasure trove of biodiversity and natural beauty. Home to the largest freshwater lake in Sarawak, this park offers an enchanting experience for nature lovers and adventure seekers alike. The diverse ecosystems range from lush peat-swamp forests with towering stilt-rooted trees to majestic Alam forests that soar over 60 meters high.
name: Loagan Bunut National Park

detail_description: Piasau Nature Reserve, which opened its doors to the public in 2014, is conveniently located just a short 20-minute drive from the town. This emerging destination offers opportunities for leisurely trekking and walking amidst natural surroundings. Notably, it stands as Malaysia's nearest nature reserve within city boundaries and boasts a unique combination of lush greenery and beachfront access.
name: Piasau Nature Reserve
address: CXPX+5X, Piasau Camp, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

name: Boulevard Shopping Mall, Miri
address: Lot 2528, Boulevard Commercial Centre, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Tanjong Lobang Beach, nestled in the vibrant heart of Miri City, Sarawak, is a must-visit for anyone exploring Malaysia's stunning coastline. This lively beach offers a long stretch of soft sand perfect for sunbathing and picnicking with family and friends. With its proximity to the Miri Petroleum Museum, it's easily accessible from the city center.
name: Tanjong Lobang Beach

detail_description: Pantai Tanjung Lobang, also known as Brighton Beach, is a popular spot in Miri to unwind and catch the breathtaking sunset. The beach features two small piers that offer unobstructed views of the coastline and the unique seahorse lighthouse at Miri Marina. It's a favorite among locals for picnics and evening gatherings to watch the sun go down.
name: Pantai Tanjung Lobang

detail_description: Miri - Sibuti Coral Reefs National Park is a fantastic diving destination in Sarawak, offering excellent visibility of 10 to 30 meters. The park boasts stunning coral reefs and a rich variety of marine life. Divers can explore different sites such as Eve's Garden, known for its leather corals and giant anemones, and Belais Reef, where angelfish, lizardfish, and batfish can be spotted.
name: Miri - Sibuti Coral Reefs National Parks

detail_description: Ming Cafe Miri Borneo is a popular spot for food enthusiasts and party-goers alike. The extensive menu offers a variety of dishes, including both Western and local stir-fry cuisine. It's known for its lively atmosphere, exciting music, and cozy environment, making it an ideal place to unwind. Whether you're looking for a late-night hangout or a chill spot to de-stress, Ming Cafe has got you covered.
name: Ming Cafe Miri Borneo

detail_description: Bungai Beach, located just a 40-minute drive from Miri City, is a beautiful spot with a lovely stretch of beach. Despite the rainy weather during one visitor's trip, they could imagine it being a cheery spot under the bright sun. The beach offers facilities like small homestays for overnight stays and is perfect for family gatherings and short escapes.
name: Bungai Beach

detail_description: Chapter One Cafe in Miri, Sarawak is a beloved spot among locals. It's the town's first library-themed cafe, offering a unique experience where you can enjoy freshly brewed coffee surrounded by books. The interior is cozy and peaceful, making it an ideal place for studying or working. Divided into two areas by a bookshelf wall, the cafe has a calming ambiance with earthy decor. While most of the menu consists of desserts, they also offer tasty food at moderate prices.
name: Chapter One Cafe
address: Lot 2288, Jalan Marina 2 1, Marina Square 2 Marina Parkcity, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Beach Republic is a pleasant destination with a beautiful beach that's not overcrowded like other beaches. The food is satisfactory, although the delivery time can sometimes be excessively long. It's an ideal spot to unwind and catch the stunning sunset view, offering amenities such as a gym and swimming pool. Moreover, there's a private room available for hosting exclusive parties, though the food and drinks may be slightly pricey.
name: Beach Republic

detail_description: Located along Jalan Brooke, the Miri Handicraft Centre has gained popularity among both locals and tourists as a renowned attraction. This small centre showcases the exceptional craftsmanship of the Dayak people in Sarawak through their traditional handmade products, particularly textiles and handbags. Visitors can immerse themselves in Sarawak's vibrant culture while exploring and purchasing various items at this centre. From colourful baskets to traditional decorations and souvenirs, there is a wide range of choices available here.
name: Miri Handicraft Center
address: Jalan Brooke, Miri Handicraft Centre, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

excerpt: Popular area featuring a small water park, a suspension bridge & playground, plus picnic space.
detail_description: Taman Awam Miri, also known as Miri Public Park, is a popular destination located 3km beyond the city center. It offers a variety of attractions for visitors of all ages. The park features a small water park with water slides and a shallow pool, making it an ideal spot for kids to cool off. Additionally, there are playgrounds and picnic areas available for families to enjoy. For those seeking adventure, the park boasts jogging trails and botanical gardens to explore.
name: Taman Awam Miri
address: Long Lapok Tinjar baram, Taman Awam Miri, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Tusan Cliff Sarawak offers a picturesque beach with a cliff and stunning scenery. However, it is not suitable for small children due to the slippery slope and lacks facilities such as shelters, toilets, or bathing areas. Visitors are advised to be cautious of excavation and drilling works nearby. Despite the recent collapse of the giant sandstone arch, the beach remains a peaceful spot with clear sands and a windy atmosphere.
name: Tusan Cliff Sarawak
CHIN FLOWER GARDEN
address: 1916, Jalan Riam Willow, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Taman Awam is a well-known spot in Miri City Resort City, perfect for morning workouts and evening strolls. It's also a popular destination for barbeque outings, attracting many visitors. Families particularly enjoy the free swimming pool, making it an ideal vacation spot for both kids and adults. Additionally, it offers various recreational activities and is a great place for sightseeing.
name: Taman awam
address: Jln Grand Park 3A, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Restoran Ayam Penyet Ria is a popular local eatery celebrated for its authentic Indonesian smashed chicken dish, Ayam Penyet. This traditional Indonesian delicacy features fried chicken that's been tenderized by smashing it with a pestle and mortar.
name: Restoran Ayam Penyet Ria
address: Lot 1326, Groundfloor , Block 9 MCLD, Miri Waterfront Commercial Centre, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Miri Central Market is a must-visit place in Miri City, offering a bustling local market scene and a variety of experiences. Visitors can explore the market's diverse offerings, from handicrafts like keychains and ethnic gear to delicious local food at the hawker area. The market also features stalls serving flavorful dishes like fried kway teow with braised pork and mixed pork soup. Additionally, visitors can find a local shop that grinds coffee beans nearby.
name: Miri Central Market

detail_description: Taman Awam Miri, also known as Miri Public Park, is located just 3km (2mi) beyond the city center. It's a great place for kids with a suspension bridge offering treetop views and access to pretty gardens. The park features a water playground with a large shallow pool, water slides, and a water fountain for kids to cool off in.
name: Taman Awam Miri

excerpt: Sprawling mall housing a supermarket, fast-food options, local handicrafts stores & a cinema.
name: Bintang Megamall
address: Lot 1264, Jalan Miri Pujut, Bintang Jaya, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Peliau Beach is a popular coastal spot near Bekenu, south of Miri, offering stunning sunset views over the South China Sea. The beach is known for its beautiful and serene ambiance, making it an ideal location for picnics and family outings. Visitors can enjoy the shade of trees along the beach, as well as amenities such as toilets, barbecue benches, a children's playground, and local stalls selling goods. The area also features picturesque rock formations that add to its tranquil atmosphere.
name: Peliau Beach

detail_description: Emart Tudan is an exceptional and distinctive shopping center known for its single-floor, open-air design that distinguishes it from conventional multi-level structures. It stands out by offering diverse sections catering to different product types, including vegetables, fish, meat, and other food items. In addition to a supermarket section and various stores, the market also showcases a wide range of local vegetables and general merchandise.
name: Emart Tudan
address: Block B, Phase 3, Emart Commercial Centre, Jln Tudan, Tudan, 98100 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: The Summit Cafe in Miri offers a diverse dining experience with a range of Japanese, Asian, and native dishes. The cafe is known for its inviting ambience and delicious menu, featuring options like ramen and authentic jungle foods. With its popularity evident from the bustling crowds, it's recommended to visit early to savor the delightful offerings.
name: The Summit Cafe

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Borneo, Piasau Boat Club is a premier hub for sports and leisure enthusiasts. This vibrant destination offers an impressive array of activities such as sailing, diving, fishing, rowing, and various ball sports that cater to all ages. It's not just about the action; the club also features a fantastic bar and restaurant where you can indulge in both Asian and Western cuisine while enjoying the company of fellow members.
name: Piasau Boat Club
address: Lot 1273, Piasau Nature Reserve, Kelab Layar, Piasau, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Canada Hill, also known as Bukit Telaga Minyak, is a significant landmark in Miri, Malaysia. It holds historical importance as the site of Malaysia's first oil drill in 1910, which played a pivotal role in shaping the country's economy. The Grand Old Lady, a replica of the initial oil well, stands tall at the hill's summit. Visitors can enjoy breathtaking panoramic views of Miri town and its surroundings from Canada Hill.
name: Canada Hill MIRI Landmark
address: Petronas Museum, Q659, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

name: OYO 90220 River Inn
address: Lot 652, Jalan Nakhoda Gampar, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

excerpt: Protected expanse of mountainous rainforest  known for huge limestone caves & rock pinnacles.
detail_description: Gunung Mulu National Park is a vast expanse of mountainous rainforest renowned for its massive limestone caves and rock pinnacles. The park offers friendly staff, pleasant garden rooms, and diverse but average food options. Local cafes and restaurants are available nearby, with the option of luxury dining at the Marriott. Visitors can support local people by exploring the well-curated information about biodiversity in the park, which effectively communicates scientific concepts to non-specialized audiences.
name: Gunung Mulu National Park

excerpt: National park in the jungle, with mature trees, hiking trails, waterfalls & bird watching.
detail_description: Taman Negara Bukit Lambir is a national park located in the jungle, offering mature trees, hiking trails, waterfalls, and bird watching opportunities. It's about an hour's drive from Miri, although road works along the route can make the journey less smooth. The park features reasonably signposted tracks with some missing signs to the HQ part of the way.
name: Taman Negara Bukit Lambir
address: 1-76, Bintulu - Miri Hwy, 98000 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia

detail_description: Pantai Tusan Bekenu, located about 40 km from Miri, is a unique and popular beach known for its stunning natural phenomena. The beach offers a long stretch of coastline where visitors can enjoy the beauty of the South China Sea while sipping on coconut milk. Perched high above the mountain, it provides a breathtaking 180-degree aerial view. A walk down to the seaside allows for an up-close experience with the saltwater and waves.
name: Pantai Tusan Bekenu
address: Exit Jalan Bekenu - Miri Coastal, 98150 Miri, Sarawak, Malaysia
